The paper discusses the impact of antenna height and site selection on the performance of Ultra Dense Networks (UDN) in downlink. This topic is closely related to the field of network infrastructure (NI) in computer science. The paper also analyzes the probability of coverage, average cell rate, and average area spectral efficiency, which are topics in information theory (IT) and systems and control (SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the deployment of regular and random base stations, which is related to multimedia (MM) and computer networks and communications (COM).
